    <h2>How To...</h2>
    <h4>Where can I find help?</h4>
    <p>Only God will help you...</p>
    <p>Still you can try to ask a question to code@spotseo.ru. Perhaps fate will smile ...</p>
    <h4>How to ssh into virtual machine?</h4>
    <p>Open your terminal (e.g. iTerm2 or Powershell) application and change to the directory with your SDD copy to "environment". Then simply execute next command:</p>
    <ol class="code">
      <li>$ vagrant ssh</li>
    </ol>
    <h4>How to get access to phpmyadmin & mysql?</h4>
    <p>Login to MySQL Server: root</p>
    <p>Password to MySQL Server specified in the file "/environment/roles/local.json"</p>
    <p>Then execute next commands in your terminal:</p>
    <ol class="code">
      <li>host$ vagrant ssh</li>
      <li>vagrant guest$ sudo mysql -u root</li>
      <li>mysql> USE mysql;</li>
      <li>mysql> UPDATE user SET plugin='mysql_native_password' WHERE User='root';</li>
      <li>mysql> FLUSH PRIVILEGES;</li>
      <li>mysql> exit;</li>
    </ol>
    <h4>How to quickly install Drupal 7?</h4>
    <p>Make shure that appropriate site exists in config.json file. Don't forget to run 'vagrant provision' after changing config.json.</p>
    <ol class="code">
      <li>host$ vagrant ssh</li>
      <li>vagrant guest$ rm -rf ~/sites/drupal7</li>
      <li>vagrant guest$ cd ~/sites</li>
      <li>vagrant guest$ drush dl drupal-7 --drupal-project-rename="drupal7"</li>
      <li>vagrant guest$ drush @drupal7 si standard -y</li>
    </ol>
